sentence: So you thought I did n't mean what I said .
mut.sentence: So you actually thought I did n't really mean what I said.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'mean'的含义是相同的。'mean'在这里指的是说话者表达的真实意图或信念。原句和变异句都使用了否定形式'didn't mean'，并且变异句中添加了'really'来加强语气，但这并不改变'mean'这个词的基本含义。因此，两个句子中的'mean'含义没有不同。

sentence: According to final closing figures , the Dow Jones Industrial Average has risen by 65.67 points to 10 471.50 points , whereas the NASDAQ , with a technology predominance , fell by 0.55 point to 2 190.31 points .
mut.sentence: According to the latest closing figures, the Dow Jones Industrial Average has edged up by 65.67 points to 10,471.50 points, whereas the NASDAQ, characterized by a technology predominance, slipped by 0.55 point to 2,190.31 points.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'closing' 的含义是一致的。'closing' 在这里指的是股票市场收盘时的数据或数字。原句中的 'final closing figures' 和变异句中的 'latest closing figures' 都表示的是最新的收盘数据，没有体现出含义上的差异。

sentence: Ringing does become a bit of an obsession , `` admits Stephanie Pattenden , master of the band at St. Mary Abbot and one of England 's best female ringers .
mut.sentence: Ringing does indeed become a bit of an obsession, '' openly admits Stephanie Pattenden, the accomplished master of the band at St. Mary Abbot and one of England's most skilled female ringers.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'band'的含义没有改变。在这两个上下文中，'band'指的是一个由St. Mary Abbot教堂的Stephanie Pattenden领导的乐队或铃声团队，她在英格兰是最优秀的女性铃声制造者之一。两个句子中的'band'都指代同一个组织或团体，没有体现出含义上的差异。

sentence: I 'd have to sell out my business to pay her off with her share .
mut.sentence: I would reluctantly have to sell out my business to fully pay her off with her share.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'pay' 的含义是相同的。'pay off' 通常是偿还债务或满足某项财务义务的意思。原句和变异句中的 'pay her off with her share' 都表达了用她应得的那份钱来偿付某事。变异句中添加的 'fully' 并没有改变 'pay' 的基本含义，只是强调了偿付的彻底性，而原句则没有这个强调。但是，这并不影响 'pay' 这个词本身的含义。

sentence: On Costa Rican side , and close to Michael Umana , are the left-lateral Junior Diaz , with 48 matches and the striker Bryan Ruiz , with 45 .
mut.sentence: On the Costa Rican side, closely matching Michael Umana in games played, are the left-lateral Junior Diaz, who has featured in 48 matches, and the striker Bryan Ruiz, with a total of 45.
reason: 原句中的'matches'指的是球员参加的比赛场次，而变异句中的'matching'是动词形式，表示与Michael Umana的比赛场次相匹配或接近，含义上存在动词与名词的差异，因此两个句子的目标词含义不同。

sentence: It was blurred , after two hours of steady drinking , but the occasion of it came back to him .
mut.sentence: It was blurredly remembered, after two hours of steady drinking, but the occasion of it eventually came back to him.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'drinking'的含义没有改变。在原句和变异句中，'drinking'都是指持续饮酒的行为，与之后的动作或状态（记忆模糊或记忆逐渐恢复）相关，但'drinking'本身的含义没有区别。

sentence: His shout had been involuntary , something anybody might have done without thinking , on the spur of the moment .
mut.sentence: His loud shout had been quite involuntary, something anybody might have impulsively done without much thinking, on the spur of the moment.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'thinking'的含义是相同的。它指的是在行动之前进行的有意识的思考或考虑。原句和变异句都表达了同样的概念，即他的叫喊是在没有经过深思熟虑的情况下，一时冲动所为。变异句中的'much thinking'只是对原句中的'thinking'进行了轻微的强调，但本质上两个词的含义没有改变。

sentence: The day the Supreme Court gathered behind closed doors to consider the politically divisive question of whether it would hear a challenge to President Obama 's healthcare law , two of its justices , Antonin Scalia and Clarence Thomas , were feted at a dinner sponsored by the law firm that will argue the case before the high court .
mut.sentence: The fateful day the Supreme Court assembled in private to ponder the politically charged question of whether to hear a challenge to President Obama's landmark healthcare law, two of its esteemed justices, Antonin Scalia and Clarence Thomas, were honored at a lavish dinner hosted by the law firm that is set to argue the pivotal case before the esteemed high court.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'question'都指的是关于是否听取对奥巴马总统医疗保健法的挑战的问题，两个句子中的'question'在语境中的含义没有区别。

sentence: According to a nationwide survey taken a year ago , nearly a third of England 's church bells are no longer rung on Sundays because there is no one to ring them .
mut.sentence: According to a comprehensive nationwide survey conducted a year ago, nearly a third of the church bells across England are no longer rung on Sundays due to the lack of bell ringers.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'longer' 的含义是相同的。'No longer' 在两个句子中都表示 '不再' 的意思，指的是过去有而现在没有了的情况，即教堂的钟声在周日不再被敲响。

sentence: It gives a lot of flexibility to the process , said John Coequyt , senior Washington representative for the Sierra Club .
mut.sentence: It provides a significant amount of flexibility to the process, according to John Coequyt, a seasoned Washington representative for the Sierra Club.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'flexibility' 在两个句子中的含义没有改变，都指的是过程中具有的灵活性。两个句子只是使用了不同的形容词（a lot of 和 significant amount of），但这两个形容词在这里都可以表示程度上的大量，因此并没有改变目标词的含义。

sentence: He wondered how he got tied up with this stranger .
mut.sentence: He idly wondered how he had got tied up with this complete stranger.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'got'的含义相同，都表示过去发生的事情，即他与这个陌生人产生联系的方式。原句和变异句中的'got'都是指过去式的不及物动词短语'get tied up'，意为'与...纠缠不清'或'与...产生联系'。变异句中添加的副词'idly'只表示他好奇心的程度，并不改变'got'本身的含义。

sentence: Haney watched the small but wiry man slip out the door quickly and silently , and felt relieved to see that nobody else seemed to notice his departure .
mut.sentence: Haney carefully watched the small yet wiry man stealthily slip out the door, and felt greatly relieved to observe that nobody else appeared to notice his quiet departure.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'slip'的含义是相同的。'slip'在这里都指的是某人轻巧、秘密或不引人注意地离开。原句和变异句中的语境都表达了这个人迅速且安静地离开了房间，而且都没有被人注意到。因此，尽管变异句中添加了一些如'carefully'、'stealthily'和'quiet'的副词来进一步强调行动的谨慎性，但并没有改变'slip'这个词的基本含义。

sentence: But what do we mean , specifically , by `` creativity `` ?
mut.sentence: But exactly what do we mean, specifically, by the term `` creativity ''?
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'mean'的含义是相同的。'mean'在这里都是指理解或解释某个概念的意思，原句和变异句中的目标词没有改变其基本含义，只是变异句在'mean'前面加上了定冠词'the term'来指代前面的“creativity”，但这并不影响'mean'这个词本身的含义。

sentence: The next day , Sunday , the hangover reminded Haney where he had been the night before .
mut.sentence: The following day, which was Sunday, the lingering hangover reminded Haney of where he had been the previous night.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'reminded'含义相同，都表示'使某人想起'。两个句子中的'reminded'都是指由于宿醉，Haney回想起了前一晚他在哪里。变异句中只是增加了'lingering'（持续的）这个形容词来描述宿醉，并且用'of'替换了'where'，但这并不改变'reminded'本身的意思。

sentence: Her critics have pushed for Kagan to recuse herself from hearing the case , saying that she was too invested in defending the law then to be impartial now .
mut.sentence: Her persistent critics have pushed for Kagan to recuse herself from hearing the crucial case, arguing that she was too deeply invested in defending the law at that time to be truly impartial now.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'case'的含义没有发生变化。'case'在原句和变异句中都指的是需要被审理的具体诉讼案件。两个句子中的其他词汇变化（如原句中的'saying'变为变异句中的'arguing'，以及添加了'persistent'和'crucial'作为修饰词）并不影响目标词'case'的含义。

sentence: In their filing , they referred to the Supreme Court 's 1966 decision overturning Dr. Sheppard 's conviction because of the trial coverage and made it clear they would claim that the new media required new rules .
mut.sentence: In their comprehensive filing, they specifically referred to the landmark Supreme Court's 1966 decision that overturned Dr. Sheppard's controversial conviction, citing the extensive trial coverage, and firmly stated that the emerging new media necessitated the adoption of new rules.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'decision'的含义没有发生变化。在原句和变异句中，'decision'都指的是1966年最高法院作出的关于推翻Sheppard博士有罪判决的决定。两个句子中的差异主要在于描述该决定的额外细节和强化了语气，但并没有改变'decision'本身的含义。

sentence: The notion that tracking is somehow `` undemocratic `` is absurd .
mut.sentence: The absurd notion that tracking is somehow inherently `` undemocratic '' is truly laughable.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'absurd'的含义没有发生变化。'absurd'用来形容一个观点或想法是荒谬的、不合理的。在原句中，'is absurd'直接说明了这个观点是荒谬的；在变异句中，'the absurd notion'也指这个想法是荒谬的。两个句子中的'absurd'都用来表达同样的意思，即对'tracking is somehow undemocratic'这一观点的否定。

sentence: The others here today live elsewhere .
mut.sentence: The others who are here today actually live elsewhere.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'today'含义相同，都指的是说话时的当天。两个句子中的'today'没有因为加入'actually'或其他语境因素而改变其基本含义。

sentence: But C.J.B. Marshall , vicar of a nearby church , feels the fault is in the stairs from the bell tower that are located next to the altar .
mut.sentence: But C.J.B. Marshall, the vicar of a nearby church, strongly feels that the fault lies in the stairs from the bell tower, which are conveniently located right next to the altar.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'stairs'的含义没有发生变化。两个句子都在描述从钟楼到圣坛旁边的楼梯，并且没有通过上下文或添加的修饰语改变楼梯本身的含义。变异句中添加的'conveniently'一词只是强调了楼梯位置的便利性，并不影响'stairs'这个词的含义。

sentence: Phil usually went alone and kept to himself , sitting in a corner and passing the time by nursing his favorite grudges .
mut.sentence: Phil typically went alone and secluded himself, quietly sitting in a dim corner and killing time by nursing his favorite grudges.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'time'的含义是相同的。'pass the time'和'kill time'都是习惯用语，表示消磨时间、打发时间，没有体现出意义上的差异。
